Preconditions:
- The input string `moves` is not null.
- The length of the input string `moves` is greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 50.
- The input string `moves` consists only of characters `'L'`, `'R'`, and `'_'`.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the distance from the origin of the furthest point reached after `n` moves.
- The furthest point can be reached by moving either to the left or to the right based on the characters in the input string `moves`.
- If the character in `moves` is `'L'`, the method moves to the left.
- If the character in `moves` is `'R'`, the method moves to the right.
- If the character in `moves` is `'_'`, the method can choose to move either to the left or to the right.
- The method calculates the distance from the origin by keeping track of the current position and updating it based on the moves made.
- The method returns the maximum distance reached from the origin after `n` moves.